{
  "stem": "22869.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it doesn't take that in-- in seven weeks, you're still capable of-- of eating, so to say, from one self.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If you  had any fat on yourself, it, like, you sustained yourself-- sustained yourself.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The-- the-- I made a friendship there, I remember, in camp, with a guy who used to be a baker, at home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he usually was trying to give me a little bit of hope by saying that one day, maybe, he'll get a place in a bakery, and then I'll have enough food.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was a dream, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I remember they came out one day with an announcement that they're looking for young people with various trades to be taken to some other destination, unknown.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were looking for bakers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So he-- he-- he adamantly begged me I should also announce myself that I'm a baker and I'll stick with him, and he'll teach me everything about it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And, sure enough, that was seven weeks later, after the arrival, which was on the Shavuos holiday, on 1942, where we were all lined up and, again, started going back to the train with the same clogs and the same loading up.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we took that trip to Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I told I was a baker.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Except-- except the Germans, in concentration camps, use the same trick that even today the American army is using.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They'll come in, they ask who is a musician, and 15 guys will raise their hands.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they'll tell them, OK, you're the detail for the latrine cleaning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I lost-- I lost sight of him, but he never came back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He did not go with me to Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He stayed there, and I never heard of him again.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
